						               													<description>A classic board game playing pantomime or answering trivia questions on Greek and International Cinema. In a round metal box (cinematic bobbin), 2 packages of 100 photos, original dashboard, wooden pawns and dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board has a similar use as with trivia games, there is no start and end, but it's purpose is to stop over different frames (places) to be asked different questions about the movie between: &amp;quot;title&amp;quot; by doing pantomime or verbally by looking at the picture, &amp;quot;director&amp;quot;, and &amp;quot;actors/actresses&amp;quot;. For that, a pawn and a dice are used giving you the option to select the type of questions that you are most familiar with. One side of the card is showing a scene from the movie, while the other has the title, director and actors/actresses involved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a movie card is played, the player/team has to answer the question to win it. If he/she/they can't reply then the next player has the opportunity to do so, etc. A movie card never returns to the pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to collect as many movie cards as possible throughout the game. The game ends if all the cards from the deck are finished of when the predefined time has passed. The player with the most cards on hand is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
